            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I tried implementing support for `file://` by doing it the same way that netrw does: creating a `BufReadCmd` autocommand for the pattern `file://*`. Turns out that the netrw way has bugs; it needs to create a new buffer to work. See `nvim --clean file:///test +ls!`.\n\nUnless someone can find a way around this, I believe this means we need to build in `file://` support a bit more directly than a plugin, so `file://` URIs are transparently converted without side effects. Ideally, `nvim /etc/foo` and `nvim file:///etc/foo` are identical.",
