            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It seems we are facing a dilemma. As mentioned earlier, implementing this in `path.c` would lead to reimplementing part of the `vim.uri_*` logic, but that's not all.\n\nMany LSP servers provide `file://` links (e.g., in hover docs), and more importantly, these `file://` links often include extensions that append `L1` to represent a single line or `L1-L3` to represent a range. Therefore, I have a work-in-progress local branch that provides `vim.uri_to_pos` and `vim.uri_to_range` to support this in Lua. If we support `file://` links in C, then:\n\n* If we support the `L1-L3` usage, it will increase the complexity of the C implementation. This is because `vim.pos`/`vim.range` are not available in C, nor is there a built-in way to open a file and jump directly to a specific line.\n* If we do not support the `L1-L3` usage, then the C implementation's support for `file://` links will be inconsistent with Lua.",
