        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It feels wrong to integrate known-buggy behavior from netrw into Nvim core, but I suppose as long as it serves as a stepping stone towards a better implemention, it's fine. Especially since there are still a few ways that the `BufReadCmd` method can be improved, such as `:bwipe`ing the temporary buffer so it doesn't appear in `:ls!`.\n\nIf that is the direction we decide to go in, I can continue working on it.",
