        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Maybe I'm not understanding the use case correctly here, but _why_ do we want to special-case `file:///` and even add support in path.c? Curl can handle reading these files. Writing is not supported, but this can be easily special-cased from the `BufWriteCmd`.\n\nI haven't seen a good point on why we want to resolve `file:///` URIs to their actual file. To me, `file:///tmp/a` and `/tmp/a` are two different things, even if they point to the same entity. E.g. `scp://localhost:/tmp/a` also points to `/tmp/a`. Do we want to special case that too?",
            "created_at": "2026-04-28T08:31:48Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39278#issuecomment-4333598273",
            "id": 4333598273,
